# 🛡️ AI-Powered Fraud Detection System

An enterprise-style Fraud Detection System that uses Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to detect fraudulent transactions in real time.

## 🚀 Features

- AI-Based Fraud Detection
- Behavioral Analysis
- Risk Scoring
- Real-Time Transaction Monitoring
- Admin Dashboard
- User Dashboard
- Email OTP Verification
- Fraud Alerts
- Transaction Analytics
- PostgreSQL Database Integration

---

# 🏗️ Tech Stack

## Frontend
- Angular
- TypeScript
- Chart.js

## Backend
- Spring Boot
- Spring Data JPA
- WebSocket
- Java Mail Sender

## Database
- PostgreSQL

## AI / Machine Learning
- Python
- Flask
- Scikit-Learn
- Joblib

---

# 📁 Project Structure

```text
fraud-detection/
│
├── fraud-frontend/        # Angular Frontend
│
├── fraud-detection/       # Spring Boot Backend
│
└── fraud-ml/             # Flask AI Service
```

---

# ⚙️ Prerequisites

Install the following before running the project:

- Java 21+
- Maven
- PostgreSQL
- Node.js
- Angular CLI
- Python 3.11+

---

# 🗄️ Database Setup

Create PostgreSQL database:

```sql
CREATE DATABASE frauddb;
```

Update database credentials inside:

```text
src/main/resources/application.properties
```

Example:

```properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/frauddb
spring.datasource.username=postgres
spring.datasource.password=YOUR_PASSWORD
```

---

# 🤖 AI Service Setup (Flask)

Navigate to AI folder:

```bash
cd fraud-ml
```

Create virtual environment:

### Windows

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate environment:

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install pandas scikit-learn flask joblib  
```

Run Flask server:

```bash
python app.py
```

AI Service starts on:

```text
http://localhost:5000
```

---

# ☕ Backend Setup (Spring Boot)

Navigate to backend folder:

```bash
cd fraud-detection
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
mvn clean install
```

Run application:

```bash
mvn spring-boot:run
```

Backend starts on:

```text
http://localhost:8080
```

---

# 🌐 Frontend Setup (Angular)

Navigate to frontend folder:

```bash
cd fraud-frontend
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Run Angular application:

```bash
ng serve
```

Frontend starts on:

```text
http://localhost:4200
```

---

# 📧 Email OTP Configuration

Enable:

- Google 2-Step Verification
- Google App Password

Add the following in:

```text
application.properties
```

```properties
spring.mail.host=smtp.gmail.com
spring.mail.port=587

spring.mail.username=YOUR_GMAIL@gmail.com
spring.mail.password=YOUR_APP_PASSWORD

spring.mail.properties.mail.smtp.auth=true
spring.mail.properties.mail.smtp.starttls.enable=true
```

---

# ▶️ Running the Complete System

Start the services in the following order:

### 1️⃣ PostgreSQL

Make sure PostgreSQL service is running.

### 2️⃣ Flask AI Service

```bash
python app.py
```

### 3️⃣ Spring Boot Backend

```bash
mvn spring-boot:run
```

### 4️⃣ Angular Frontend

```bash
ng serve
```

---

